==Russian==

===Noun===
'''гопник''' (gópnik), [[гопники]] (gópniki) {{p}}

# a member of the Russian urban criminal subculture '''[[гопники]]'''; a young [[hoodlum]], a member of a street [[gang]].
# a young [[bully]], a [[rowdy]] youth.
# an aggressive, poorly educated and [[ill-mannered]] person, even if not so young.

